com.enremmeta.rtb.api

Interface Ad

  • All Superinterfaces:
    KVKeysValues, Lot49Constants, Lot49Plugin, RtbConstants
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdImpl, AdImplTest.Ad_1111_fake, AdITTest.Ad_181818_fake, AdTest.Ad_1234_segments, AdTest.Ad_181818_fake, BidCandidateManagerSpec.Ad_1001001_fake2, IntegralTest.Ad_1010_integral_fake, SharedSetUp.Ad_1001001_fake, SharedSetUp.Ad_1001001_mock

    public interface Ad
extends Lot49Plugin

    Specifies ad configuration. Most functionality is implemented in AdImpl. An Ad may have one or more Tags.

    It is intended that simple Groovy (but not necessarily) scripts extend those classes class, filling in tag information (e.g., Dimension, etc.) and the actual tag text.

    1. The naming convention is such that it's named Ad_<AdId>_<AdName>.
    2. Ad config is the one that can be returned from getId().
    3. init() method sets up the necessary fields which will be checked in canBid1(OpenRtbRequest).

      • canBid1

        boolean canBid1(OpenRtbRequest bidRequest)
        Whether this can target this particular bid request. Important notes:
        1. This MUST NOT check all of the constituent config 's canBid() methods. This only qualifies the bid request's attributes (including user) in absence of a particular ad tag configuration. Thus, on a test bid, all of these methods can be assumed to be true, but not all canBid()s.
        2. This only checks that information that can be checked without external lookup; in other words, it should not presume that Lot49Ext.getLot49ExtRemote() is populated.
        3. If either this method returns false, this targeting configuration is not eligible to bid.

        This will always return true if bidRequest is a test request.

      • checkSegments

        boolean checkSegments(OpenRtbRequest br,
                      UserSegments userSegments)
        Whether this can target this particular bid request (but different from canBid1(OpenRtbRequest). Important notes:
        1. This MUST NOT check all of the constituent config 's canBid() methods. This only qualifies the bid request's attributes (including user) in absence of a particular ad tag configuration. Thus, on a test bid, all of these methods can be assumed to be true, but not all canBid()s.
        2. This will not be called if needCanBid2() is false.
        3. If either this method or canBid1(OpenRtbRequest) returns false, this ad is not eligible to bid.

        This will always return true if bidRequest is a test request.
        See Also:
        canBid1(com.enremmeta.rtb.api.proto.openrtb.OpenRtbRequest)

      • getBidProbability

        int getBidProbability()
        Between 0 and 100. Probability of bidding for pacing purposes. Set to 0 to never bid, and to 100 to bid always (subject to getBidFrequency(). Values below 0 and above 100 work the same as 0 and 100 respectively.
        See Also:
        getBidFrequency()
